s been unequivocally successful and debates between approaches persist. The Material Theory of Induction identifies the source of these enduring problems in the assumption taken at the outset: that inductive inference can be accommodated by a single formal account with universal applicability. Instead, it argues that that there is no single, universally applicable formal account. Rather, each domain has an inductive logic native to it.The content of that logic and where it can be applied are determined by the facts prevailing in that domain. Paying close attention to how inductive inference is conducted in science and copiously illustrated with real-world examples, The Material Theory of Induction will initiate a new tradition in the analysis of inductive inference.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aInduction (Logic). 0aInference. 0aLogic. 7aSCIENCE / Philosophy & Social Aspects.2bisacsh  abooks about philosophy of science.  abooks about science.  abooks for scientists.  achance.  adeductive inference.  adeductive logic.  ahistory of science.  ainductive inference.  ainductive logic.  ainductive support.  amaterial theory of induction.  anew theory of induction.  aphilosophy of science.  aprobability.  astudy of chance.  astudy of probability.  astudy of science.  atheory of induction.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311127221408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021z978311127464540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781773852553?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781773852553423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781773852553/original  a978-3-11-127221-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-127464-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021b20